eanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Richers was born in 1520, in Bungay, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of John Richers. She married Andrew Stubbes in 1540, in Sedgeford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in Sedgeford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1520–":"1520–Surnud","1520–Female":"1520–Surnud","1515–Male":"1515–Surnud","1546–Male":"1546–Surnud","1490–Male":"1490–Surnud","1546":"1546","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1490":"1490","1515":"1515","Sedgeford, , Norfolk, England":"Sedgeford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bungay, , Suffolk, England":"Bungay, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1520–":"1520–Kuollut","1520–Female":"1520–Kuollut","1515–Male":"1515–Kuollut","1546–Male":"1546–Kuollut","1490–Male":"1490–Kuollut","1546":"1546","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1490":"1490","1515":"1515","Sedgeford, , Norfolk, England":"Sedgeford, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bungay, , Suffolk, England":"Bungay, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1520–":"1520–Décédée","1520–Female":"1520–Décédée","1515–Male":"1515–Décédé","1546–Male":"1546–Décédé","1490–Male":"1490–Décédé","1546":"1546","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1490":"1490","1515":"1515","Sedgeford, , Norfol